    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Wait, \"long-overdue correction\"? That sounds like you're definitely taking a side. What about the people who argue that the \"living constitution\" approach is more appropriate for a modern society? Don't they have a valid point that the Founders couldn't have anticipated modern weaponry?",
