      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The \"living constitution\" argument is a sophisticated way of saying the Constitution is a flexible document that must adapt to modern realities. While the Founders certainly didn't envision assault rifles, their intent was to protect the *function* of the right, which is self-defense against modern threats. Therefore, the Court's modern interpretations are not just arbitrary; they are necessary to ensure the amendment remains relevant and effective in the 21st century.",
      "source": "target",
